    {
      "id": "97afe808_d2d9f7d5",
      "file_path": "policy-db-migrator/src/main/docker/config/policyadmin/sql/0900/downgrade/0120-JpaPolicyAuditIndex_timestamp.sql",
      "patchset_number": 6,
      "line": 20,
      "message": "wouldn't it still generate an error when FK checks are re-enabled?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2021-07-13 14:14:03.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "9f72f3c4_5796b719",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "6f72511e_ba0f745e",
      "file_path": "policy-db-migrator/src/main/docker/config/policyadmin/sql/0900/downgrade/0120-JpaPolicyAuditIndex_timestamp.sql",
      "patchset_number": 6,
      "line": 20,
      "message": "No it doesn't.\nThe script will run to the end and all indexes, constraints and tables are dropped.\nWithout it the script fails on the first downgrade script because they are run in reverse order.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7668,
        "name": "Kevin Timoney",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "kevin.timoney@est.tech",
        "username": "ktimoney"
      },
      "updated": "2021-07-13 14:20:27.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "97afe808_d2d9f7d5",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "da54917c_12436e0d",
      "file_path": "policy-db-migrator/src/main/docker/config/policyadmin/sql/0900/downgrade/0120-JpaPolicyAuditIndex_timestamp.sql",
      "patchset_number": 6,
      "line": 20,
      "message": "I'm imagining this scenario:\n\n  script 1:\n    set FK=0\n    drop index 1\n    set FK=1\n\n  script 2:\n    set FK=0\n    drop index 2\n    set FK=1\n\nif dropping index 1 causes a violation, then I would expect it to generate a violation as soon as FK=1 is executed, which happens before script 2 is executed",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2021-07-13 14:25:18.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "6f72511e_ba0f745e",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "98a8789a_401853ac",
      "file_path": "policy-db-migrator/src/main/docker/config/policyadmin/sql/0900/downgrade/0120-JpaPolicyAuditIndex_timestamp.sql",
      "patchset_number": 6,
      "line": 20,
      "message": "I'm not sure what's going on behind the scenes.\nThere isn't very much documentation on line for this error.\nI think when you run SET FOREIGN_KEY_CHECKS = 0; it disables all foreign keys\nand SET FOREIGN_KEY_CHECKS = 0 re-enables them.\nThe constraint itself is created independently and exist prior to the index.\nI assume when you create the index it creates some kind of binding between the index and constraint.\nWhen the index is removed the constraint exists again independently and is re-enabled without the index.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7668,
        "name": "Kevin Timoney",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "kevin.timoney@est.tech",
        "username": "ktimoney"
      },
      "updated": "2021-07-13 14:40:44.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "da54917c_12436e0d",
      "unresolved": true
    },
